1 WHEREAS, utilizing information from citizens, employees, and stakeholders in all
2 levels of government is a necessary collaboration to achieve a more responsible and
3 efficient government in Kentucky;
4 NOW, THEREFORE,
5 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the General Assembly of the
6 Commonwealth of Kentucky, the Senate concurring therein:
7 Section 1. The Legislative Research Commission is hereby directed to create
8 the Kentucky Discipline of Government Efficiency (KY DOGE) Task Force. The
9 Discipline of Government Efficiency Task Force is directed to study and examine
10 Executive Branch expenditures to identify opportunities to increase efficiency in the
11 delivery of government operations and inform the biennial budget preparation process.
12 Section 2. The task force shall be composed of the following 10 members, with
13 final membership of the task force being subject to the consideration and approval of the
14 Legislative Research Commission:
15 (1) Four members of the Senate to be appointed by the President of the Senate, one
16 of whom shall be designated as a co-chair of the task force by the President of the Senate;
17 (2) One member of the Senate, to be appointed by the Minority Floor Leader of
18 the Senate;
19 (3) Four members of the House of Representatives to be appointed by the Speaker
20 of the House of Representatives, one of whom shall be designated as a co-chair of the
21 task force by the Speaker of the House; and
22 (4) One member of the House of Representatives to be appointed by the Minority
23 Floor Leader of the House of Representatives.
24 Section 3. The Kentucky Discipline of Government Efficiency Task Force shall
25 meet at least monthly during the 2025 Interim of the General Assembly and shall submit
26 its findings, legislative recommendations, or recommendations to the Legislative
27 Research Commission no later than December 1, 2025. If legislative recommendations
